UI_visible_response: "Under the Dome" is a science fiction novel written by Stephen King, first published in 2009. The story is set in the small town of Chester's Mill, Maine, where an invisible and indestructible dome suddenly encapsulates the town, cutting it off from the rest of the world. The novel explores the psychological and societal effects of this event on the town's residents, as well as the struggle for power and survival within the confined space.The book was adapted into a television series of the same name, which aired on CBS from 2013 to 2015. The TV series, while based on King's novel, diverges in several plot points and character developments.In addition to its narrative content, "Under the Dome" has also been noted for its environmental and political themes, reflecting concerns about authority, governance, and human impact on the environment.
